article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 91, Long Beach St. 75
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Josh Akognon and Frank Robinson each scored 18 points to lead Cal State Fullerton to a 91-75 victory over Long Beach State Thursday. The Titans (13-6, 6-2 Big West Conference) have won three straight games. Akognon scored four 3-pointers. Robinson made 8 of 13 baskets, including four baskets early in the second half, that gave the Titans a 69-55 lead with 12:35 remaining. Marcus Crenshaw scored 17 points and Scott Cutley added 14 for the Titans. Marcus Morgan had 10 rebounds for Cal State Fullerton, who outrebounded Long Beach State 36-34 in the game. Donavan Morris led the 49'ers (4-15, 1-6) with 31 points, while Maurice Clady added 13. Long Beach State erased a seven point deficit in the first half and then went on a 23-9 run to take a 31-24 lead with 6:30 left on a 3-pointer by Morris. Cal state Fullerton battled back and took a 49-43 lead at the break.
